<TITLE> Ctg river ports reel under wildcat strike </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 18 (bdnews24.com) Goods unloading and transportation have been suspended in 16 river ports of Chiittagong, after the pier and storage workers went on a wildcat strike since Monday morning. Chittagong Ghat Gudam Sramik Union president Abdul Kader told bdnews24.com they were striking for a pay rise. Kader said a workers gets Tk 7.20 for unloading a 90 kg sack in four steps from releasing the goods from lighter ships to truck. They wanted it hiked to Tk 10. The strike would be withdrawn as soon as the demand was accepted, he added. MA Latif MP, president of Chittagong Chamber of Commerce and Industries, told bdnews24.com the 'wildcat' strike would affect unloading of imported goods from vessels. bdne
